HEADWORD: Seaboat
<hw>Sea"boat`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[AS.
<ets>s⟦aemac⟧b⟦amac⟧t</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A boat or vessel
adapted to the open sea; hence, a vessel considered with reference to
her power of resisting a storm, or maintaining herself in a heavy sea;
<as>as, a good <ex>sea boat</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A chiton.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Seabord</ent>⟦br⟧
